		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">[14]</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<paragraph height="0" width="605" y="+16" x="12"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT SIZE="2"></FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="1" id="1">
			<answer correct="false">A  Between 1980 and 1984 the number of children with divorced parents fell by around 14,500.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="2" id="2">
			<answer correct="false">B  By 1975 the number of children whose parents were divorced had reached 145,096.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="3" id="3">
			<answer correct="true">C  By 1981 the number of first marriages per year had fallen by over 100,000.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="4" id="4">
			<answer correct="true">D  From 1994 to the end of the period the number of children with divorced parents declined steadily.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="5" id="5">
			<answer correct="false">E  In 1971 the number of remarriages was just over 10,000 higher than the number of divorces.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="6" id="6">
			<answer correct="false">F  In 1991 the number of divorces was almost 50,000 higher than the figure for remarriages in the same year.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="7" id="7">
			<answer correct="true">G  The number of children whose parents were divorced nearly doubled between 1970 and 1972.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="8" id="8">
			<answer correct="true">H  The number of children with divorced parents reached a peak in 1993.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="9" id="9">
			<answer correct="false">I  The number of children with divorced parents was approximately the same in 1979 as it was in 1983.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="10" id="10">
			<answer correct="false">J  The number of divorces in 1991 was almost equal to the number of first marriages in 1999.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="11" id="11">
			<answer correct="true">K  The number of divorces in 1999 was double the number in 1971.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="12" id="12">
			<answer correct="true">L  The number of first marriages in 1999 was less than half the number in 1971.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="13" id="13">
			<answer correct="true">M  The number of remarriages declined steadily after 1981.</answer>
		</field>
		<field mode="0" type="i:target" group="14" id="14">
			<answer correct="true">N  There was a 25 per cent increase in the number of children whose parents were divorced between 1972 and 1978.</answer>
		</field>
